&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/leitourgia/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/terms/leitourgia/> ;
  schema:name "Leitourgia" ;
  schema:description "A Leitourgia is a quadruple (λ, φ, C, ι) — a designated agent in Hohfeldian liability position, a prescribed-form proposition in the fiber Heyting algebra, a witnessing community constituted by a covering family in the Grothendieck topology, and a discharge proposition. Full discharge is ι ∈ H*_t: past-settled (saturation-nucleus-fixed) and forward-stable (transfer-nucleus-fixed) simultaneously. The personal cost is the Landauer cost of the settling step: spectral mass of the kernel of the counit." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-19" ;
